sql:
SELECT p.player_id, p.player_name
FROM players p
JOIN (
    SELECT player_id, AVG(runs) AS avg_runs
    FROM player_statistics
    GROUP BY player_id
) ps ON p.player_id = ps.player_id
WHERE ps.avg_runs > (
    SELECT AVG(runs) FROM player_statistics
);

external_knowledge:
- Standout players refer to those who were awarded the "man of the match.";
- Concluded matches refer to matches with a "completed" status.;
- The order from most recent to the oldest is determined by the match dates.
